    <p>
        Are you tired and frustrated with not being able to lose weight?&nbsp; Do you feel like no matter what 
        you do, you are not making any progress improving your symptoms?&nbsp; I understand; I have worked with 
        MANY women who went through the same thing.  
    </p>
    <p>If you’re like many of the women I work with, you:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Wonder WHY this is happening to you</li>
        <li>Feel like you cannot truly enjoy eating without feeling guilty or deprived</li>
        <li>Fear that you may not be able to have children</li>
        <li>Feel overwhelmed by all the possible “risk” factors</li>
        <li>Want to feel healthy, but don’t know how</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        I can personally relate to some of these things because when I was a teenager, my doctor’s solution to my irregular 
        cycles and acne was to simply put me on birth control pills.
    </p>
    <p>
        I didn’t find out about PCOS until I started working in health care almost ten years ago as a registered and licensed 
        dietitian.&nbsp; I started having clients who were having symptoms that I remembered going through.&nbsp; I realized 
        then that I needed to learn as much as I could about the condition so that I could help not only my clients, but myself 
        as well. 
    </p>

    <p>
        I've completed well over 40 hours of continuing education through two different PCOS experts, and I continue to study 
        the condition to this day.  I am happy to say that I have been able to keep virtually all of my lab values and weight 
        within normal limits and feel as healthy as ever.  What’s just as great is the number of women I have worked with who 
        have also been able to turn their lives around and experience relief from many of their symptoms.
    </p>
    <p>
        Sadly, there are still not many nutritionists who have expertise in PCOS.&nbsp; That’s why I created <i>The 5 Step 
        Formula for Overcoming PCOS</i>.&nbsp; My program will teach you:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Exactly how PCOS is diagnosed and how it is different from other similar conditions
            so that you can feel confident that you are <strong>getting the right treatment</strong>
            and not wasting time! </li>
        <li>How foods affect your hormones so that you know <strong>what</strong> to eat and
            <strong>when</strong> to eat to help you lose weight and feel great. </li>
        <li>What health care providers you should have on your team to <strong>help you prevent
            complications</strong> and reach your goals in the safest, quickest way and what
