            your whole body healthy. </li>
        <li>How to know which supplements may improve your symptoms</li>
        <li>How to prevent serious side effects from interactions between foods or supplements and medications potentially
            used to treat PCOS.</li>
        <li>What to do to once you reach your goals!</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        One of the best things about my program is that you can learn at your own pace, while having the support of other women 
        who are going through the same things.&nbsp; You will have the opportunity to ask questions every week in our group 
        coaching calls, as well as make connections with other participants.
    </p>

    <p class="testimonial">
        “Just want to let you know that your PCOS webinar was great. I listened to the recorded
        version last night, took tons of notes and plan to listen again. Thank you for sharing
        your info.” – Christine C. Williams, RD; Potomac MD
    </p>

    <p>Not taking action now could cost you <strong>thousands and thousands of dollars</strong> due to needing:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>More doctors’ appointments</li>
        <li>More medications</li>
        <li>More time away from family or work</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        But it can also cost you more than just time and money.&nbsp; Every day that you <strong>wait</strong> to learn how 
        to overcome your PCOS you <strong>increase</strong> your risk of:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Developing Heart Disease</strong></li>
        <li>Developing Diabetes</li>
        <li><strong>Not being able to have children</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <p>
